This paper deals with channel coding and error exponents, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC) subfields of computer science. The paper also discusses the performance of the codebooks in the presence of noise and erasures, which falls under the subfields of signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the results for practical applications, which could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) subfield.
